obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (2528)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189&sectionId=2528&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Tobacco Board`
  line `Act, 1975.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint:`
  line
  line `Provided that different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act and for different`
  line `States or different parts thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 28th August, 1976, vide notification No. S.O. 3141, dated 20th August, 1976, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3(ii).`
  line
  line `This Act has been extended to the States of Andhra Pradesh and Karnataka in respect of ss. 10 and 11 and ss. 12, 14 and 15`
  line `in the whole of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (2529)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Declaration as to expediency of control by the Union.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189&sectionId=2529&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `It is hereby declared that it is expedient`
  line `in the public interest that the Union should take under its control the tobacco industry.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (2530)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189&sectionId=2530&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Board" means the Tobacco Board established under section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) "Chairman" means Chairman of the Board;`
  line
  line `(c) "curing" shall have the meaning assigned to it in the Central Excises and Salt Act,`
  line `1944 (1 of 1944) and all its grammatical variations and cognate expressions shall be construed`
  line accordingly;
  line
  line `(d) "dealer" means a dealer in tobacco;`
  line
  line `(e) "Executive Director" means the Executive Director appointed under section 6;`
  line
  line `(f) "export" and import mean, respectively, taking out of, or bringing into, India, by land, sea or`
  line air;
  line
  line `(g) "member" means a member of the Board and includes the Chairman;`
  line
  line `(h) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(i) "registered" means, except in the expression registered grower, registered under Chapter III`
  line `of this Act and the rules made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(j) "registered grower" means a person who has obtained a certificate of registration under`
  line `section 10 for growing virginia tobacco.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (2531)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Establishment and constitution of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189&sectionId=2531&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint in this behalf, there shall be established`
  line `for the purposes of this Act, a Board to be called the Tobacco Board.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall be a body corporate by the name aforesaid, having perpetual succession and a`
  line `common seal, with power to acquire, hold and dispose of property, both movable and immovable, and to`
  line `contract, and shall by the said name sue and be sued.`
  line
  line `^1[(3) The head office of the Board shall be at Guntur in the State of Andhra Pradesh and the Board`
  line `may, with the previous approval of the Central Government, establish offices or agencies at other places`
  line `in or outside India.]`
  line
  line `(4) The Board shall consist of the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a Chairman to be appointed by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) three members of Parliament, of whom two shall be elected by the House of the People and`
  line `one by the Council of States;`
  line
  line `(c) ^2[eight] members to be appointed by the Central Government to represent respectively:--`
  line
  line `(i) the Ministry of the Central Government dealing with Agriculture;`
  line
  line `(ii) the Ministry of the Central Government dealing with Commerce;`
  line
  line `(iii) the Ministry of the Central Government dealing with Finance;`
  line
  line `(iv) the Ministry of the Central Government dealing with Industrial Development;`
  line
  line `(v) the Indian Council of Agricultural Research;`
  line
  line `(vi) the Government of Andhra Pradesh; ^3***`
  line
  line `^4[(via) the Government of Gujarat; and]`
  line
  line `(vii) the Government of Karnataka;`
  line
  line `(d) two members to be appointed by the Central Government, by rotation in the alphabetical`
  line `order, to represent the Governments of tobacco-growing States ^5[other than the States of Andhra`
  line `Pradesh, Gujarat and Karnataka;]`
  line
  line `(e) not more than ^5[ten members] to be appointed by the Central Government from amongst`
  line `growers of tobacco, dealers and exporters (including packers) of tobacco and tobacco products,`
  line `manufacturers of tobacco products and from amongst persons who, in the opinion of the Central`
  line `Government, are experts in tobacco marketing or agricultural economics:`
  line
  line `^6[Provided that the number of members appointed under this clause from amongst the growers of`
  line `tobacco shall not exceed six.]`
  line
  line `^6[(f) the Agricultural Marketing Adviser to the Government of India, Department of Rural`
  line `Development, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(g) the Executive Director, ex officio.]`
  line
  line `^7[(4A) It is hereby declared that the office of member of the Board shall not disqualify its holder for`
  line `being chosen as, or for being, a member of either House of Parliament.]`
  line
  line `(5) The Board shall elect, from amongst its members, a Vice-Chairman who shall exercise such of the`
  line `powers and perform such of the functions of the Chairman as may be prescribed or as may be delegated to`
  line `him by the Chairman.`
  line
  line `(6) The term of office of the members and the manner of filling vacancies among, and the procedure`
  line `to be followed in the discharge of their functions by, the members shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(7) ^8[Any officer] of the Central Government (not being a member of the Board) as is deputed by the`
  line `Central Government in this behalf, shall have the right to attend the meetings of the Board and take part`
  line `in the proceedings thereof, but shall not have the right to vote.`
  line
  line `(8) The Board may associate with itself, in such manner and for such purposes as may be prescribed,`
  line `any persons whose assistance or advice it may desire in complying with any of the provisions of this Act`
  line `and a person so associated shall have the right to take part in the discussions of the Board relevant to the`
  line `purposes for which he has been associated, but shall not have the right to vote.`
  line
  line `(9) No act or proceeding of the Board or any committee appointed by it under section 7 shall be`
  line `invalidated merely by reason of--`
  line
  line `(a) any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of, the Board or such committee; or`
  line
  line `(b) any defect in the appointment of a person acting as a member of the Board or such committee;`
  line or
  line
  line `(c) any irregularity in the procedure of the Board or such committee not affecting the merits of`
  line `the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by Act 36 of 1978, s. 2, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 30-8-1978).`
  line
  line `2 Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "seven" (w.e.f. 30-8-1978).`
  line
  line `3. The word "and" omitted by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 30-8-1978)`
  line `4. Ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 30-8-1978).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "other than the States of Andhra Pradesh and Karnataka" (w.e.f. 30-8-1978)./nr`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 57 of 1985, s. 2, for "eight members" (w.e.f. 1-12-1985).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-12-1985).`
  line
  line `8 Subs. byAct 57 of 1985, s. 2, for "The Executive Director and any such officer" (w.e.f. 1-12-1985).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (2532)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Salary and allowances and other conditions of service of Chairman.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189&sectionId=2532&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `The Chairman shall be`
  line `entitled to such salary and allowances and such conditions of service in respect of leave, pension,`
  line `provident fund and other matters as may, from time to time, be fixed by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (2533)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Officers of the Board and other staff.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189&sectionId=2533&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall appoint an Executive`
  line `Director to exercise such powers and perform such duties under the Chairman as may be prescribed or as`
  line `may be delegated to him by the Chairman.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall appoint a Secretary to the Board to exercise such powers and`
  line `perform such duties under the Chairman as may be prescribed or as may be delegated to him by the`
  line Chairman.
  line
  line `(3) The Executive Director and the Secretary shall be entitled to such salaries and allowances and`
  line `such conditions of service in respect of leave, pension, provident fund and other matters as may from time`
  line `to time be fixed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to such control, restrictions and conditions (including conditions as to appointment of the`
  line `officers and other employees of the Tobacco Export Promotion Council, in the event of the said Council`
  line `being wound up) as may be prescribed, the Board may appoint such other officers and employees as may`
  line `be necessary for the efficient performance of its functions.`
  line
  line `(5) The Chairman, the Executive Director, the Secretary and other officers and employees of the`
  line `Board shall not undertake any work unconnected with their duties under this Act except with the`
  line `permission of the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (2534)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Committees of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189&sectionId=2534&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may appoint such committees as may be necessary for`
  line `the efficient discharge of its duties and performance of its functions under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall have the power to co-opt as members of any committee appointed under`
  line `sub-section (1) such number of persons who are not members of the Board as it may think fit and the`
  line `persons so co-opted shall have the right to attend the meetings of the committee and take part in the`
  line `proceedings of the committee but shall not have the right to vote.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (2535)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Functions of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189&sectionId=2535&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be the duty of the Board to promote, by such measures as it`
  line `thinks fit, the development under the control of the Central Government of the tobacco industry.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the provisions of sub-section (1), the measures referred to`
  line `therein may provide for--`
  line
  line `^1[(a) regulating the production and curing of virginia tobacco having regard to the following`
  line `factors, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) the demand for virginia tobacco in India and abroad;`
  line
  line `(ii) the suitability of land for growing virginia tobacco;`
  line
  line `(iii) the differences in soil characteristics and agro-climatic factors in different regions of the`
  line `country where virginia tobacco is grown and the effect thereof on the quality and quantity of`
  line `virginia tobacco produced in those regions;`
  line
  line `(iv) the marketability of different types of virginia tobacco;`
  line
  line `(v) the need for rotation of crops; and`
  line
  line `(vi) the nature of the holdings of the growers of virginia tobacco whether owned or leased;`
  line
  line `(b) keeping a constant watch on the virginia tobacco market, both in India and abroad, and`
  line `ensuring that the growers get a fair and remunerative price for the same and that there are no wide`
  line `fluctuations in the prices of the commodity;`
  line
  line `(c) maintenance and improvement of existing markets, and development of new markets outside`
  line `India for Indian virginia tobacco and its products and devising of marketing strategy in consonance`
  line `with demand for the commodity outside India, including group marketing under limited brand names;`
  line
  line `^2[(cc) establishment by the Board of auction platforms, with the previous approval of the Central`
  line `Government, for the sale of virginia tobacco by registered growers or curers, and functioning of the`
  line `Board as an auctioneer at auction platforms established by or registered with it subject to such`
  line `conditions as may be specified by the Central Government;]`
  line
  line `(d) recommending to Central Government the minimum prices which may be fixed for purposes`
  line `of export of virginia tobacco with a view to avoiding unhealthy competition amongst the exporters;`
  line
  line `(e) regulating in other respects virginia tobacco marketing in India and export of virginia tobacco`
  line `having due regard to the interests of growers, manufacturers and dealers and the nation;`
  line
  line `(f) propagating information useful to the growers, dealers and exporters (including packers) of`
  line `virginia tobacco and manufacturers of virginia tobacco products and others concerned with virginia`
  line `tobacco and products thereof;`
  line
  line `(g) purchasing virginia tobacco from growers when the same is considered necessary or expedient`
  line `for protecting the interests of the growers and disposal of the same in India or abroad as and when`
  line `considered appropriate;`
  line
  line `(h) promoting the grading of tobacco at the level of growers;`
  line
  line `(i) sponsoring, assisting, co-ordinating or encouraging scientific, technological and economic`
  line `research for the promotion of tobacco industry;`
  line
  line `(j) such other matters as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Without prejudice to the generality of the provisions of sub-section (1) and subject to priority`
  line `being given to matters specified in sub-section (2), the measures referred to in sub-section (1) may also`
  line `provide in relation to tobacco, other than virginia tobacco, for all or any of the matters specified in`
  line `clauses (c) to (g) of sub-section (2) and for this purpose any reference in those clauses to virginia tobacco`
  line `shall be construed as including a reference to tobacco other than virginia tobacco.`
  line
  line `(4) The Board shall perform its functions under this section in accordance with and subject to such`
  line `rules as may be made by the Central Government and such rules may in particular make provisions for`
  line `ensuring that the Board functions in close liaison with Union agencies, institutions and authorities`
  line `concerned with the tobacco industry (including growing of tobacco) and avoids duplication of effort.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for clause (a) (w.e.f. 1-12-1985).`
  line
  line `2 Ins. by Act 36 of 1978, s. 3 (w.e.f. 30-8-1978).`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (2536)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Dissolution of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189&sectionId=2536&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette and for reasons to be specified therein, direct that the Board shall be dissolved from such date and`
  line `for such period as may be specified in the notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that before issuing any such notification, the Central Government shall give a reasonable`
  line `opportunity to the Board to make representations against the proposed dissolution and shall consider the`
  line `representations, if any, of the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) When the Board is dissolved under the provisions of sub-section (1),--`
  line
  line `(a) all members, notwithstanding that their term of office has not expired, shall, from the date of`
  line `dissolution, vacate their offices as such members;`
  line
  line `(b) all powers and duties of the Board shall, during the period of dissolution, be exercised and`
  line `performed by such person or persons as the Central Government may appoint in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(c) all funds and other properties vested in the Board shall, during the period of dissolution, vest`
  line `in the Central Government; and`
  line
  line `(d) as soon as the period of dissolution expires, the Board shall be reconstituted in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (2537)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Registration of growers of virginia tobacco.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189&sectionId=2537&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall grow virginia tobacco except`
  line `under, and in accordance with, the conditions of a certificate of registration obtained from the Board in`
  line `accordance with the rules made under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In granting or refusing a certificate of registration, the Board shall have regard to the demand for`
  line `virginia tobacco in India and abroad, and the suitability of the land in relation to which the certificate is`
  line `applied for and such other factors as may, having regard to the needs of the virginia tobacco industry, be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(3) A certificate of registration granted in pursuance of this section shall be valid for such period as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) Every application for such certificate of registration shall be accompanied by such fees (not`
  line `exceeding one rupee for 0.4 hectare of the land in relation to which such application has been made) as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10_a:
  sectionId (2538)
  sectionNo 10A
  orderNo 11
  title `Registration of growers of virginia tobacco seedlings for commercial purposes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 57 of 1985, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-12-1985).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189&sectionId=2538&sectionno=10A&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189
obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[10A. Registration of growers of virginia tobacco seedlings for commercial purposes.-- (1) No`
  line `person shall grow virginia tobacco seedlings for commercial purposes unless he registers himself as a`
  line `nursery grower with the Board in accordance with the rules made under this Act.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that nothing in this sub-section shall`
  line `apply to the growing by a registered grower of any virginia tobacco seedlings for his own use.`
  line
  line `(2) No registered nursery grower shall sell or cause to be sold any virginia tobacco seedlings grown`
  line `by him to any person other than a registered grower.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (2539)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 12
  title `Registration of curers of virginia tobacco.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189&sectionId=2539&sectionno=11&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `No person other than a registered curer shall cure`
  line `or undertake the curing of virginia tobacco unless he registers himself as a curer with the Board in`
  line `accordance with the rules made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11_a:
  sectionId (2540)
  sectionNo 11A
  orderNo 13
  title `Registration of processors and manufacturers of virginia tobacco, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_a_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-12-1985).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189&sectionId=2540&sectionno=11A&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189
obj_root_law_sections_11_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[11A. Registration of processors and manufacturers of virginia tobacco, etc. -- No person shall`
  line `process virginia tobacco or manufacture products therefrom unless he registers himself as such processor`
  line `or manufacturer, as the case may be with the Board in accordance with the rules made under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_b:
  sectionId (2541)
  sectionNo 11B
  orderNo 14
  title `Licences to be obtained for grading work and construction of barns, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_b_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-12-1985).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189&sectionId=2541&sectionno=11B&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189
obj_root_law_sections_11_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[11B. Licences to be obtained for grading work and construction of barns etc.-- No person`
  line shall--
  line
  line `(i) take up grading work relating to virginia tobacco for commercial purposes; or`
  line
  line `(ii) take up the construction and operation of a barn,`
  line `unless he obtains a licence from the Board in accordance with the rules made under this Act.`
  line
  line `Explanation. -- For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(i) "barn" means a building or structure with a roof of zinc sheets or tiles having flue pipes,`
  line `furnace and tiers used for flue curing of tobacco leaves;`
  line
  line `(ii) "grading work" means separating tobacco leaves into specific grades on the basis of plant`
  line `position, maturity, colour, body and blemish and in accordance with such specifications as may be`
  line prescribed.]
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (2542)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 15
  title `Registration of exporters, packers, auctioneers and dealers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189&sectionId=2542&sectionno=12&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `No person shall export tobacco`
  line `or any tobacco products or function as a packer, auctioneer of, or dealer in, tobacco unless he registers`
  line `himself with the Board in accordance with the rules made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (2543)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 16
  title `Virginia tobacco to be sold at registered auction platforms`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 36 of 1978, s. 4 (w.e.f. 30-8-1978).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189&sectionId=2543&sectionno=13&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `No registered grower or curer`
  line `shall sell or cause to be sold virginia tobacco elsewhere than at an auction platform registered with the`
  line `Board in accordance with the rules made under this Act ^1[or established by the Board under this Act].`
obj_root_law_sections_13_a:
  sectionId (20392)
  sectionNo 13A
  orderNo 17
  title `Duty of registered dealers and exporters to purchase at auction platforms, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_a_content
  footnotes `1 . Ins. by Act 57 of 1985, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-12-1985).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189&sectionId=20392&sectionno=13A&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189
obj_root_law_sections_13_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[13A. Duty of registered dealers and exporters to purchase at auction platforms, etc.-- No`
  line `registered dealer or registered exporter shall purchase or cause to be purchased virginia tobacco`
  line elsewhere--
  line
  line `(a) than at an auction platform registered with the Board in accordance with the rules made under`
  line `this Act or established by the Board under this Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) than from any other registered dealer or a registered grower or curer:`
  line
  line `Provided that in relation to any State in which the provisions of section 13 are not in force, the`
  line `condition specified under clause (a) shall not apply.]`
obj_root_law_sections_13_b:
  sectionId (20393)
  sectionNo 13B
  orderNo 18
  title `Duty or buyers of virginia tobacco at places other than auction platforms to refrain from certain unfair practices`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_b_content
  footnotes `1 . Ins. by Act 57 of 1985, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-12-1985).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189&sectionId=20393&sectionno=13B&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189
obj_root_law_sections_13_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[13B. Duty of buyers of virginia tobacco at places other than auction platforms to refrain from`
  line `certain unfair practices.-- Every dealer who purchases virginia tobacco in any State in which the`
  line `provisions of section 13 are not in force,--`
  line
  line `(a) shall pay the full price for the whole quantity of virginia tobacco so purchased by him at the`
  line `rate at which he agreed to purchase such tobacco and shall refrain from claiming any discount in the`
  line `weight or other deductions in weight thereof or any deductions from the price as calculated in`
  line `accordance with such rate;`
  line
  line `(b) shall pay the full price for virginia tobacco so purchased by him as calculated in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of clause (a) as expeditiously as possible and in any case within such reasonable`
  line `time as may be specified in this behalf by the Board; and`
  line
  line `(c) shall refrain from having recourse to any practices which the Board may, having regard to the`
  line `need for protection of persons selling virginia tobacco in such State and all other relevant`
  line `considerations, specify to be unfair practices.]`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (20394)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 19
  title `Application, cancellation, fees and other matters relating to registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189&sectionId=20394&sectionno=14&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `The form of`
  line `application and the form of certificate of registration under section 10, the form of application ^1[for`
  line `registration of nursery growers for the purposes of section 10A, for registration of curers for the purposes`
  line `of section 11, for registration of processors and manufacturers for the purposes of section 11A, for`
  line `obtaining licences for taking up grading work or construction and operation of barns under section 11B],`
  line `for registration of exporters, packers or auctioneers of, or dealers in, tobacco, for the purposes of`
  line `section 12, and for registration of auction platforms for the purposes of section 13, the time within which`
  line `and the manner in which such applications shall be made, the fees payable on such applications, the`
  line `particulars to be specified therein, the principles and the procedure to be followed in granting and`
  line `cancelling certificates of registration or the registration of auction platforms or, as the case may be, ^2[the`
  line `registration as nursery growers, curers, processors, exporters, packers or auctioneers of, or dealers in, virginia tobacco or as manufacturers of the products of virginia tobacco or in granting licences under`
  line `section 11B, the returns to be submitted and the registers to be maintained by registered growers, nursery`
  line `growers, curers, processors, exporters, packers or auctioneers of, or dealers in, virginia tobacco or the`
  line `registered manufacturers of the products of virginia tobacco or the persons licensed under section 11B`
  line `and the registers to be kept by the Board shall be such as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for "for registration of curers for the purposes of section 11" (w.e.f. 1-12-1985).`
  line
  line `2 Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for certain words (w.e.f. 1-12-1985).`
obj_root_law_sections_14_a:
  sectionId (20395)
  sectionNo 14A
  orderNo 20
  title `Power to levy fees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_a_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 36 of 1978, s. 5 (w.e.f. 30-8-1978).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189&sectionId=20395&sectionno=14A&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189
obj_root_law_sections_14_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[14A. Power to levy fees.-- (1) Where virginia tobacco is sold at any auction platform established by`
  line `the Board under this Act, it shall be competent for the Board or for any officer of the Board authorised by`
  line `it in this behalf to levy fees, for the services rendered by the Board in relation to such sale, at such rate not`
  line `exceeding two per cent. of the value of such tobacco as the Central Government may, from time to time,`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette, specify.`
  line
  line `(2) The fees levied under sub-section (1) shall be collected by the Board or such officer, equally from`
  line `the seller of the virginia tobacco and the purchaser of such tobacco, in such manner as may be`
  line prescribed.]
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (20396)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 21
  title `Power of inspection`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189&sectionId=20396&sectionno=15&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `The Board may authorise any of its members, officers or other employees`
  line `to inspect in such manner as may be prescribed any land or premises to verify the accuracy of any`
  line `particulars mentioned in any application or any return referred to in section 14.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (20397)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 22
  title `Grants and loans by the Central Government`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189&sectionId=20397&sectionno=16&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, after due`
  line `appropriation made by Parliament by law in this behalf, pay to the Board by way of grants or loans such`
  line `sums of money as the Central Government may think fit for being utilised for the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (20398)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 23
  title `Constitution of the Tobacco Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189&sectionId=20398&sectionno=17&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be formed a Fund to be called the Tobacco`
  line `Fund and there shall be credited thereto--`
  line
  line `(a) the fees levied and collected under this Act or the rules made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(b) any sums of money paid or any loans granted by the Central Government for the purposes of`
  line `this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) any grants or loans that may be made by any person for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) the sums, if any, realised by the Board in carrying out the measures referred to in section 8.`
  line
  line `(2) The Fund shall be applied--`
  line
  line `(a) for meeting the cost of the measures referred to in section 8;`
  line
  line `(b) for meeting the salaries, allowances and other remuneration of the officers and other`
  line `employees of the Board;`
  line
  line `(c) for meeting the other administrative expenses of the Board;`
  line
  line `(d) for repayment of any loans.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (20399)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 24
  title `Borrowing powers of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189&sectionId=20399&sectionno=18&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `Subject to such rules as may be made in this behalf, the`
  line `Board shall have the power to borrow on the security of the Tobacco Fund or any other asset for carrying`
  line `out the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18_a:
  sectionId (20400)
  sectionNo 18A
  orderNo 25
  title `Writing off of losses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_a_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 57 of 1985, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-12-1985).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189&sectionId=20400&sectionno=18A&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189
obj_root_law_sections_18_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[18A. Writing off of losses.-- Subject to such conditions as may be specified by the Central`
  line `Government, where the Board is of opinion that any amount due to, or any loss, whether of money or of`
  line `property, incurred by, the Board is irrecoverable, the Board may, with the previous approval of the`
  line `Central Government, sanction the writing off finally of the said amount or loss:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such approval of the Central Government shall be necessary where such`
  line `irrecoverable amount or loss does not exceed in any individual case and in the aggregate in any year such`
  line `amounts as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (20401)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 26
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes `1 . Subs. by Act 57 of 1985, s. 9, for "profit and loss account" (w.e.f. 1-12-1985).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189&sectionId=20401&sectionno=19&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall maintain proper accounts and other relevant records`
  line `and prepare an annual statement of accounts, including the ^1[income and expenditure account] and the`
  line `balance-sheet in such form as may be prescribed by the Central Government in consultation with the`
  line `Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the Board shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India at`
  line `such intervals as may be specified by him and any expenditure incurred in connection with such audit`
  line `shall be payable by the Board to the Comptroller and Auditor-General.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and any person appointed by him in connection`
  line `with the audit of the accounts of the Board shall have the same rights and privileges and authority in`
  line `connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General has in connection with the audit of`
  line `Government accounts and, in particular, shall have the right to demand the production of books, accounts,`
  line `connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect any of the offices of the Board.`
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the Board as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or any`
  line `other person appointed by him in this behalf together with the audit report thereon shall be forwarded`
  line `annually to the Central Government and that Government shall cause the same to be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (20402)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 27
  title `Power to prohibit or control import and export of tobacco and tobacco products.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189&sectionId=20402&sectionno=20&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make provision for prohibiting,`
  line `restricting or otherwise controlling the import or export of tobacco and tobacco products, either generally`
  line `or in specified classes of cases.`
  line
  line `(2) All tobacco and tobacco products to which any order under sub-section (1) applies, shall be`
  line `deemed to be goods of which the import or export has been prohibited under section 11 of the Customs`
  line `Act, 1962 (52 of 1962), and all the provisions of that Act shall have effect accordingly.`
  line
  line `(3) If any person contravenes any order made under sub-section (1), he shall, without prejudice to`
  line `any confiscation or penalty to which he may be liable under the provisions of the Customs Act,`
  line `1962 (52 of 1962), as applied by sub-section (2), be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to one year, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20_a:
  sectionId (20403)
  sectionNo 20A
  orderNo 28
  title `Power of Central Government to authorise purchase of virginia tobacco.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_a_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by s. 10, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-12-1985).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189&sectionId=20403&sectionno=20A&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189
obj_root_law_sections_20_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[20A. Power of Central Government to authorise purchase of virginia tobacco.--Without`
  line `prejudice to the provisions of clause (g) of sub-section (2) of section 8 and notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in any other provision of this Act, if the Central Government is satisfied that it is necessary or`
  line `expedient so to do, it may, by order in writing and subject to such conditions and limitations as may be`
  line `specified in the order, authorise any body or other agency to purchase virginia tobacco from the growers`
  line `and dispose of the same in India or abroad.]`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (20404)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 29
  title `Directions by Central Government`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189&sectionId=20404&sectionno=21&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `The Board shall carry out such directions as may be`
  line `issued to it from time to time by the Central Government for the efficient administration of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (20405)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 30
  title `Returns and reports`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189&sectionId=20405&sectionno=22&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall furnish to the Central Government at such time and`
  line `in such form and manner as may be prescribed or as the Central Government may direct, such returns and`
  line `statements and such particulars in regard to any proposed or existing programme for the promotion and`
  line `development of the tobacco industry, as the Central Government may, from time to time, require.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), the Board shall, as soon as possible, after`
  line `the end of each financial year, submit to the Central Government a report in such form and before such`
  line `date, as may be prescribed, giving a true and full account of its activities, policy and programmes during`
  line `the previous financial year.`
  line
  line `(3) A copy of the report received under sub-section (2) shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is`
  line `received, before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (20406)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 31
  title Penalties.
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189&sectionId=20406&sectionno=23&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `Any person who, being required under this Act to furnish any return, fails to furnish`
  line `such return or furnishes a return containing any particular which is false and which he knows to be false`
  line `or does not believe to be true, shall be punishable with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (20407)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 32
  title `Penalties for obstructing a member, officer or other employee of the Board in the discharge of his duties and for failure to produce books and records.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189&sectionId=20407&sectionno=24&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `Any person who--`
  line
  line `(a) obstructs any member or any officer or other employee of the Board or any other person in the`
  line `exercise of any power conferred, or in the discharge of any duty imposed, on him by or under this`
  line `Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) having control over or custody of any account book or other record, fails to produce such`
  line `book or record when required to do so by or under this Act,`
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine which`
  line `may extend to one thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (20408)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 33
  title `Other penalties`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189&sectionId=20408&sectionno=25&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `Whoever contravenes or attempts to contravene or abets the contravention of`
  line `the provisions of this Act ^1[or of any rules or regulations made thereunder] other than the provisions,`
  line `punishment for the contravention whereof has been provided for in section 20 or section 23 or section 24,`
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may ^2[extend to two years, or with fine which`
  line `may extend to five thousand rupees, or with both] and in the case of a continuing contravention with an`
  line `additional fine which may extend to fifty rupees for every day during which such contravention continues`
  line `after conviction for the first such contravention.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by Act 57 of 1985, s. 11, for "or of any rules made thereunder" (w.e.f. 1-12-1985).`
  line
  line `2 Subs. by s. 11, ibid., for "extend to six months, or with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees, or with both"`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-12-1985).`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (20409)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 34
  title `Offences by companies`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189&sectionId=20409&sectionno=26&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who, at the time the offence was committed, was in charge of, and was`
  line `responsible to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company as well as the company shall`
  line `be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished`
  line `accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he exercised all`
  line `due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be`
  line `guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation. -- For the purposes of this section`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (20410)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 35
  title `Jurisdiction of court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189&sectionId=20410&sectionno=27&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `No court inferior to that of a Metropolitan Magistrate or a Magistrate of`
  line `the first class shall try any offence punishable under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (20411)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 36
  title `Previous sanction of Central Government`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189&sectionId=20411&sectionno=28&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `No prosecution for any offence punishable under`
  line `this Act shall be instituted except with the previous sanction of the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (20412)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 37
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189&sectionId=20412&sectionno=29&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceedings shall`
  line `lie against the Central Government, or the Board or any committee appointed by it, or any member of the`
  line `Board or such committee, or any officer or other employee of the Central Government or of the Board or`
  line `any agent of or any other person authorised by the Board, for anything which is in good faith done or`
  line `intended to be done under this Act or the rules made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (20413)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 38
  title `Suspension of operation of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189&sectionId=20413&sectionno=30&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Central Government is satisfied that circumstances`
  line `have arisen rendering it necessary that certain of the restrictions imposed by this Act should cease to be`
  line `imposed or if it considers it necessary or expedient so to do in the public interest, the Central Government`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, suspend or relax to a specified extent, for such period as may`
  line `be specified in the notification, the operation of all or any of the provisions of this Act, in all or any of the`
  line `territories to which this Act extends.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the operation of any provision of this Act has, under sub-section (1), been suspended or`
  line `relaxed, such suspension or relaxation may, at any time while this Act remains in force, be removed by`
  line `the Central Government by notification in the Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(3) Every notification issued under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is issued,`
  line `before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be`
  line `comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session`
  line `immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any`
  line `modification in the notification or both Houses agree that the notification should not be issued, the`
  line `notification shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be;`
  line `so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the previous operation`
  line `of the notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (20414)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 39
  title `Application of other laws not barred.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189&sectionId=20414&sectionno=31&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall be in addition to, and`
  line `not in derogation of, the provisions of any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (20415)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 40
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189&sectionId=20415&sectionno=32&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the powers and functions of the Vice-Chairman of the Board;`
  line
  line `(b) the term of office and other conditions of service of members, the manner of filling vacancies`
  line `among, and the procedure to be followed in the discharge of their functions by, members;`
  line
  line `(c) the powers which may be exercised and the duties which shall be performed by the Executive`
  line `Director and the Secretary;`
  line
  line `(d) the circumstances in which and the authority by which a member may be removed;`
  line
  line `(e) the holding of a minimum number of meetings of the Board every year;`
  line
  line `(f) the procedure to be followed at the meetings of the Board for the conduct of business and the`
  line `number of members which shall form a quorum at a meeting;`
  line
  line `(g) the maintenance by the Board of records of business transacted by the Board and the`
  line `submission of copies thereof to the Central Government;`
  line
  line `^1[(ga) the specifications with regard to grading work referred to in section 11B;]`
  line
  line `(h) the matters referred to in section 14;`
  line
  line `^2[(hh) the manner of collection of fees under sub-section (2) of section 14A;]`
  line
  line `(i) the powers of the Board, its Chairman, the Executive Director and committees of the Board`
  line `with respect to the incurring of expenditure;`
  line
  line `(j) the conditions subject to which the Board may incur expenditure outside India;`
  line `^3[(ja) the amounts for the purposes of the proviso to section 18A;]`
  line
  line `(k) the preparation of budget estimates of receipts and expenditure of the Board and the authority`
  line `by which the estimates are to be sanctioned;`
  line
  line `(l) the form and manner in which the accounts should be maintained by the Board;`
  line
  line `(m) the deposit of the funds of the Board in banks and the investment of such funds;`
  line
  line `(n) the conditions to be observed by the Board in borrowing money;`
  line
  line `(o) the conditions subject to which, and the manner in which, contracts may be entered into by or`
  line `on behalf of the Board;`
  line
  line `(p) the additional matters in respect of which the Board may undertake measures in the discharge`
  line `of its functions;`
  line
  line `(q) the remuneration and other allowances payable to the person or persons referred to in`
  line `clause (b) of sub-section (2) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(r) the form and manner of, and the particulars to be contained in, any returns or reports to be`
  line `made to the Board under this Act;`
  line
  line `(s) the collection of any information or statistics in respect of tobacco or tobacco products;`
  line
  line `(t) any other matter which has to be, or may be, prescribed by, or provided for by rules under, this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before`
  line `each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be`
  line `comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule, or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule`
  line `shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so,`
  line `however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of`
  line `anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Ins. by Act 57 of 1985, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-12-1985).`
  line
  line `2 Ins. by Act 36 of 1978, s. 6 (w.e.f. 30-8-1978).`
  line
  line `3 Ins. by Act 57 of 1985, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-12-1985).`
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (20416)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 41
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 57 of 1985, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-12-1985).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189&sectionId=20416&sectionno=33&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00006_197504_1517807324189
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may make regulations not inconsistent with this Act`
  line `and the rules made thereunder for enabling it to discharge its functions under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may provide for all`
  line `or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the procedure to be followed at meetings of the committees appointed by the Board and the`
  line `number of members which shall form a quorum at a meeting;`
  line
  line `(b) the delegation to the Chairman, members, Executive Director, Secretary or other officers of`
  line `the Board, of any of the powers and duties of the Board under this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) the travelling and other allowances payable to persons associated under sub-section (8) of`
  line `section 4 or co-opted under sub-section (2) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(d) the pay and allowances and leave and other conditions of service of officers (other than those`
  line `appointed by the Central Government) and other employees of the Board;`
  line
  line `(e) the maintenance of the accounts of the Board;`
  line
  line `(f) the maintenance of the registers and other records of the Board and its various committees;`
  line
  line `(g) the appointment by the Board of agents to discharge, on its behalf, any of its functions;`
  line
  line `(h) the persons by whom, and the manner in which, payments, deposits and investments may be`
  line `made on behalf of the Board.`
  line
  line `^1[(i) the time within which full price for virginia tobacco shall be paid under clause (b), and the`
  line `unfair practices for the purpose of clause (c), of section 13B.]`
  line
  line `(3) No regulation made by the Board shall have effect until it has been approved by the Central`
  line `Government and published in the Official Gazette, and the Central Government, in approving a`
  line `regulation, may make any change therein which appears to it to be necessary.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, cancel any regulation which`
  line `it has approved and, thereupon, the regulation shall cease to have effect.`
  line
  line `^1[(5) Every regulation made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before`
  line `each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised`
  line `in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the regulation or both Houses agree that the regulation should not be made, the regulation shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that regulation.]`
